comments.content: It looks like Antique Black. I’m looking at it in a catalog and the only digital version I’m aware of is on the ‘ [24 Gothic Display Fonts CD](http://web.archive.org/web/20060113045837/http:/www.amazon.com/gp/product/0486999556/qid=1136935348/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_xs_ap_i1_xgl14/103-0491276-2103866?n=507846&s=books&v=glance)’.

Both [Mariage](http://web.archive.org/web/20060113045837/http:/www.linotype.com/89949/mariageregular-font.html) and [Old English](http://web.archive.org/web/20060113045837/http:/www.linotype.com/11949/oldenglishplain-font.html) are similar, but not exact.
